The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control, NCDC says 22 new cases of coronavirus, #COVID19 pandemic, have been reported. While announcing the update on its Twitter handle @NCDCGov on Wednesday evening, the Centre stated that 15 cases were reported in Lagos, four in the Federal Capital Territory, FCT, two in Bauchi and one in Edo. ‘Twenty-two new cases of #COVID19 have been reported in Nigeria: 15 in Lagos, 4 in the FCT, 2 in Bauchi, 1 in Edo “As at 09:00pm 8th April there are 276 confirmed cases of #COVID19 reported in Nigeria. Fourty-four have been discharged with six deaths,” the tweet reads.